# WHAT IT IS
#   The `stf` CLI is the **single entrypoint that launches each
#   of the 28 STF microservices** ("units") in a distributed
#   deployment.  Each unit speaks ZeroMQ to the central
#   `triproxy` (the typed input-event bus) and `poorxy` (the
#   typed output-event bus) processes, talks REST/HTTP to the
#   `app` unit for the web UI, persists state to `rethinkdb`
#   via the `log-rethinkdb` and `migrate` units, and binds
#   per-device ADB to the `provider` unit which drives the
#   minicap / minitouch / STFService.apk Android client trio.
#
#   The 28 subcommands fall into rough functional buckets:
#
#     • **Web + API**:  `app` (the web frontend), `api` (the
#       REST API server), `websocket` (the live screen
#       streamer + input-injection WebSocket front-end),
#       `poorxy` (the reverse proxy that fronts everything)
#
#     • **Authentication** (one of these must run for users
#       to log in):  `auth-ldap` (LDAP-backed auth — the
#       subcommand that's the reason STF lives on the LDAP
#       axis), `auth-oauth2`, `auth-openid`, `auth-saml2`,
#       `auth-mock` (dev-only fake auth)
#
#     • **Device control**:  `provider` (the per-host ADB-
#       attached daemon that owns physical Android devices),
#       `device` (the per-device child process spawned by
#       `provider`), `reaper` (re-attaches disconnected
#       devices), `processor` (background event handler)
#
#     • **Storage**:  `storage-plugin-apk`,
#       `storage-plugin-image`, `storage-s3`, `storage-temp`
#       (pluggable APK + image + S3 + tmp blob backends)
#
#     • **Messaging**:  `triproxy` (typed input bus),
#       `notify-slack`, `notify-hipchat`
#
#     • **Operations**:  `migrate` (run RethinkDB schema
#       migrations), `doctor` (verify cluster wiring),
#       `groups-engine` (the group-booking-quota engine),
#       `log-rethinkdb` (event-log writer)
#
#     • **Convenience**:  `local` (single-host quick-start
#       that starts most units in one process), `generate-
#       fake-device`, `generate-fake-user`,
#       `generate-fake-group` (test fixtures)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from lib/cli/index.js yargs
#                       command registrations + each
#                       lib/cli/<unit>/index.js builder block;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of lib/cli/index.js + auth-ldap/
#                       index.js)
#
#   stf <UNIT> [OPTIONS]
#
#   Standard yargs auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version (delegates to
#                                    package.json#version)
#
#   Units:
#     api                            Start the REST API server
#     app                            Start the web frontend
#     auth-ldap                      Start an LDAP auth unit
#         -a, --app-url <URL>        URL to the app unit
#                                    (required)
#         -u, --ldap-url <URL>       URL to the LDAP server
#                                    (e.g. `ldap://127.0.0.1`)
#                                    (required) [env: LDAP_URL]
#         --ldap-bind-credentials <PW>
#                                    LDAP bind credentials
#                                    [env: LDAP_BIND_CREDENTIALS]
#         --ldap-bind-dn <DN>        LDAP bind DN
#                                    [env: LDAP_BIND_DN]
#         --ldap-search-class <CLASS>
#                                    LDAP search objectClass
#                                    [default: top]
#                                    [env: LDAP_SEARCH_CLASS]
#         --ldap-search-dn <DN>      LDAP search DN (required)
#                                    [env: LDAP_SEARCH_DN]
#         --ldap-search-field <FIELD>
#                                    LDAP search field (required)
#                                    [env: LDAP_SEARCH_FIELD]
#         --ldap-search-scope <SCOPE>
#                                    LDAP search scope
#                                    [default: sub]
