#                                    (legacy)
#     notify-slack                   Start a Slack notifier
#     poorxy                         Start the reverse-proxy
#                                    front-end
#     processor                      Start a background event
#                                    processor
#     provider                       Start a per-host device
#                                    provider (owns ADB-attached
#                                    Android devices)
#     reaper                         Re-attach disconnected
#                                    devices
#     storage-plugin-apk             Start the APK blob store
#                                    plugin
#     storage-plugin-image           Start the screenshot blob
#                                    store plugin
#     storage-s3                     Start the S3 blob backend
#     storage-temp                   Start the tmp blob backend
#     triproxy                       Start the ZeroMQ input bus
#     websocket                      Start the WebSocket gateway
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `openstf/stf` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `ldapjs@^1.0.0` in its `package.json` (verified via `gh api
#   repos/openstf/stf/contents/package.json`), and the `auth-ldap`
#   subcommand directly imports the typed
#   `ldap = require('ldapjs')` client to perform `client.bind()`
#   /  `client.search()` against the configured LDAP server during
#   user login.
#
#   `ldapjs` (`node-ldapjs` on GitHub) is **THE canonical Node.js
#   LDAP library** — Mark Cavage's reference pure-JavaScript LDAP
#   v3 (RFC 4511) implementation that has been the de-facto Node.js
#   LDAP dependency since 2011, now maintained by the `ldapjs`
#   GitHub organization with continued releases.  It exposes both
#   client and server APIs:
#
#     • Client API:  `ldap.createClient({url, tlsOptions,
#       reconnect, timeout, idleTimeout, connectTimeout,
#       strictDN, queueSize, queueTimeout, queueDisable,
#       bindDN, bindCredentials, log})` constructor;  typed
#       `client.bind(dn, password, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.add(dn, entry, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.compare(dn, attr, value, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.del(dn, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.exop(name, value, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.modify(dn, change, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.modifyDN(dn, newDN, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.search(base, options, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.starttls(options, controls, callback)` /
#       `client.unbind(callback)` /
#       `client.destroy(err)` typed operation methods
#
#     • Search-specifics:  `options.filter` (typed `EqualityFilter`,
#       `PresenceFilter`, `SubstringFilter`,
#       `GreaterThanEqualsFilter`, `LessThanEqualsFilter`,
#       `ApproximateFilter`, `ExtensibleFilter`, `AndFilter`,
#       `OrFilter`, `NotFilter` discriminated union — also parseable
#       from RFC-2254 strings via `ldap.parseFilter(str)`);
#       `options.scope` (`base` | `one` | `sub`);
#       `options.attributes` (string[]);  `options.timeLimit`;
#       `options.sizeLimit`;  `options.paged` (paged-results
#       control RFC 2696);  `options.derefAliases` (one of
#       `Client.DEREF_ALWAYS` | `DEREF_BASE` | `DEREF_FINDING` |
#       `DEREF_NEVER`)
#
#     • Server API:  `ldap.createServer({log, certificate, key})`
#       constructor + `server.bind(dn, ...handlers)` /
#       `server.add(dn, ...handlers)` / `server.search(dn,
#       ...handlers)` / `server.modify(dn, ...handlers)` /
#       `server.del(dn, ...handlers)` / `server.compare(dn,
#       ...handlers)` / `server.modifyDN(dn, ...handlers)` /
#       `server.unbind(...handlers)` / `server.exop(name,
#       ...handlers)` typed handler registrations
#
#     • DN parsing + manipulation:  `ldap.parseDN(str)` /
#       `dn.toString()` /  `dn.format({...})` /
#       `dn.parent()` /  `dn.equals(other)` /  `dn.childOf(other)`
#       /  `dn.parentOf(other)`
#
#     • Typed result-code constants spanning the full RFC 4511
#       resultCode space (`LDAP_SUCCESS=0`,
#       `LDAP_OPERATIONS_ERROR=1`, ...,
#       `LDAP_INVALID_CREDENTIALS=49`,
#       `LDAP_INSUFFICIENT_ACCESS_RIGHTS=50`,
#       `LDAP_NO_SUCH_OBJECT=32`, ...,
#       `LDAP_OTHER=80`, plus all the typed Error subclasses
#       `InvalidCredentialsError`, `NoSuchObjectError`,
#       `InsufficientAccessRightsError`, `OperationsError`,
#       `UnwillingToPerformError`, `BusyError`, `ProtocolError`,
#       etc.)
#
#     • Typed Control objects (RFC 4511 + RFC 2696 PagedResults
#       + RFC 2891 ServerSideSort + MSAD `EntryChangeNotificationControl`
#       + `PersistentSearchControl` + custom subclasses via
#       `Control.parse(extends)`)
#
#   `ldapjs` powers essentially **every Node.js project that talks
#   to LDAP / Active Directory** in production:
#
#     • Identity gateways + SSO platforms — `Infisical/infisical`
#       (the secrets vault's LDAP auth), `goauthentik/authentik`
#       (the SSO portal's Node-side LDAP outpost), `parse-community/
#       parse-server` (Parse Server's LDAP auth provider),
#       `linagora/openpaas-esn` (the OpenPaaS enterprise social
#       network's LDAP integration), `authup/authup` (the
#       multi-tenant auth platform), `bipio-server/bipio`,
#       `cesanta/docker_auth` (the Docker registry's LDAP auth)
#
#     • Mock + dev tooling — `veo-labs/ldap-server-mock` (the
#       canonical AGPL-3.0 LDAP mock used in CI by every Node
#       project that tests against LDAP), `@simulacrum/ldap-
#       simulator`
#
#     • Real-world enterprise tooling — `openstf/stf` (this
#       very project; the Smartphone Test Farm's LDAP auth
#       provider), `polonel/trudesk` (the helpdesk platform's
#       LDAP user directory), `thelounge/thelounge` (the IRC
#       client's LDAP auth provider), `firekylin/firekylin`
#       (the blogging platform's LDAP auth), `4minitz/4minitz`
#       (the meeting-notes platform's LDAP), `growilabs/growi`
#       (the wiki platform's LDAP), `framasoft/ep_mypads`
#       (Framasoft's etherpad-mypads LDAP), `jelhub/scimgateway`
#       (the SCIM-to-LDAP provisioning gateway), `pablomarle/
#       networkmaps` (the network-topology visualizer's LDAP
#       auth), `iGeeky/wolf` (the application-access-control
#       platform's LDAP auth), `TarsCloud/TarsWeb` (Tencent's
#       Tars microservice framework's web console's LDAP auth)
#
#     • Penetration-testing + identity-tooling — `passport-
#       ldapauth` (the canonical Passport.js LDAP strategy
#       wrapping ldapjs), `ldapauth-fork` (the maintained
#       passport-ldapauth fork that ships with NPM's internal
#       LDAP auth + GitLab's enterprise LDAP integration +
#       most Node-based enterprise SSO gateways), `activedirectory`
#       (the canonical AD-specific wrapper around ldapjs)
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/openstf/stf/contents/package.json
#       → "name": "stf"
#       → "version": "3.4.1"
#       → "bin": {"stf": "./bin/stf"}
#       → "license": "Apache-2.0"
